docs/working/digests/README.md:3:One digest per epic. A digest is the distilled, slice-ready extract of the large files in `docs/source/` — field lists, endpoints, validation rules, role rules, and exact source-section pointers — so a normal Ralph run reads a 2–5 KB digest instead of re-reading 80–125 KB source documents.
docs/working/digests/README.md:6:- Create or extend the digest for an epic the first time one of its slices needs source material; every extraction an agent makes from `docs/source/` gets saved here.
docs/working/digests/README.md:7:- Always include the source file and section number for each fact, so anything can be verified against the source of truth.
