 | A-017 | The `GET /api/v1/audit-logs/` list orders newest-first by `created_at` with `audit_log_id` as a deterministic secondary tiebreak, uses `page_size` default 20 / max 100 (mirroring the 002G admin-user list), and rejects any query parameter outside `{entity_type, entity_id, actor_user_id, page, page_size}` with `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`. `user_agent` is stored on `AuditLog` but not exposed, matching the §42.1 item shape. | `api-contracts.md` §42.1 fixes the item fields and newest-first intent but is silent on tiebreak, page-size bounds, and unknown-parameter strictness; these are boring industry-standard defaults consistent with the existing admin list and the slice's "unknown filters return 400" rule. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §42.1; `docs/slices/003A-audit-log-foundation.md`; `sfpcl_credit/identity/modules/admin_users.py` | 003A-audit-log-foundation | Low | No | 2026-07-04 | If source docs later specify a different audit ordering, page-size ceiling, or additional filters, extend `identity/modules/audit_log.py` and its tests accordingly. |
+| A-018 | The `GET /api/v1/workflow-events/` list orders newest-first by `created_at` with `workflow_event_id` as a deterministic secondary tiebreak, uses `page_size` default 20 / max 100, and rejects any query parameter outside `{entity_type, entity_id, page, page_size}` with `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`. `record_workflow_event(...)` accepts `action_code` and `metadata` as explicit boundary facts but does not persist them because `data-model.md` §26.2 defines no action or metadata columns. | `api-contracts.md` §42.2 only names the endpoint and example filters; `data-model.md` §26.2 fixes the canonical table columns. Persisting extra action/metadata would drift from the source schema, while accepting them at the service boundary keeps callers explicit for later workflow slices. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §42.2; `docs/source/data-model.md` §26.2; `docs/slices/003B-workflow-event-foundation.md` | 003B-workflow-event-foundation | Low | No | 2026-07-05 | If source docs later add action or metadata columns, add a migration and persist those fields in `sfpcl_credit/workflows/events.py`. |
